<section
  class="mx-auto mt-16 max-w-[1240px] scroll-mt-[120px] px-6 sm:mt-24 lg:mt-[32vh] 2xl:mt-[22vh]"
  id="about"
  data-animate-group
>
  <p class="text-[14px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[#878787] sm:text-[16px]" data-animate>
    About the program
  </p>
  <h2
    class="mt-4 text-[28px] font-bold text-[#a0152a] sm:text-[32px] md:text-[64px]"
    data-animate
  >
    Access is growing. Agency is not.
  </h2>
  <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-[16px] leading-[1.6] text-[#6b6b6b] sm:text-[18px]">
    <p data-animate>
      More young people in Kenya are connected, online, and exposed to technology
      than ever before. But being connected doesn't mean you can participate
      meaningfully - it doesn't mean you can build, access capital, or plug into
      systems that let your ideas actually exist.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      HTSI exists to close that gap. We work with youth who have the ideas, the
      drive, and the understanding of real problems in their communities - and we
      give them the infrastructure, support, and pathways to execute.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      The Kenyan Development Program (KDP) is our flagship initiative on the
      African continent, built in partnership between HTSI North America and
      HTSI Africa. We're not building in parallel to existing systems - we're
      working alongside schools, local organizations, and partners already doing
      the work.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
